OL,3,CTeachers get new guidance as ministers
OL,4,C'ban' mobile phones in schools
OL,6,FThe promise was met with scepticism at
OL,7,Fthe time, and one trade union on
OL,8,FMonday branded it a "non-policy for a
OL,9,Fnon-problem".
OL,11,FIn England, it is currently up to
OL,12,Findividual heads to decide their own
OL,13,Fpolicies on mobile phones and whether
OL,14,Fthey should be banned.
OL,16,FThe guidance, which is non-statutory,
OL,17,Finstructs headteachers on how to ban
OL,18,Fthe use of phones not only during
OL,19,Flessons but during break and lunch
OL,20,Fperiods as well.
