OL,3,CTeachers get new guidance as ministers
OL,4,C'ban' mobile phones in schools
OL,6,FIt also suggests that staff could
OL,7,Fsearch pupils and their bags for
OL,8,Fmobile phones if necessary, noting
OL,9,Fthat "headteachers can and should
OL,10,Fidentify mobile phones and similar
OL,11,Fdevices as something that may be
OL,12,Fsearched for in their school behaviour
OL,13,Fpolicy".
OL,15,FIn a foreword to the document, Ms
OL,16,FKeegan said it would provide "clarity
OL,17,Fand consistency" for teachers and that
OL,18,Fthere is currently "a large variation
OL,19,Fin how different schools are managing
OL,20,Fthe use of mobile phones".
