OL,3,CTeachers get new guidance as ministers
OL,4,C'ban' mobile phones in schools
OL,6,FTom Bennet, who advises the Department
OL,7,Ffor Education on behaviour, said:
OL,8,F"Mobile phones may be ubiquitous, but
OL,9,Fwe have a strong and growing
OL,10,Funderstanding of how damaging they can
OL,11,Fbe for a child's social and
OL,12,Feducational development.
OL,14,F"And it's the least advantaged who
OL,15,Fsuffer most. Many schools already have
OL,16,Fsome kind of policy on phones, but
OL,17,Fthis guidance provides a clear steer
OL,18,Ffor everyone, including parents, about
OL,19,Fwhat's right and what's not for the
OL,20,Fwellbeing of the child.
