OL,3,CTeachers get new guidance as ministers
OL,4,C'ban' mobile phones in schools
OL,6,FHe said: "Most schools already forbid
OL,7,Fthe use of mobile phones during the
OL,8,Fschool day or allow their use only in
OL,9,Flimited and stipulated circumstances.
OL,11,F"We have lost count of the number of
OL,12,Ftimes that ministers have now
OL,13,Fannounced a crackdown on mobile phones
OL,14,Fin schools. It is a non-policy for a
OL,15,Fnon-problem.
OL,17,F"The Government would be far better
OL,18,Foff putting its energies into bringing
OL,19,Fto heel the online platforms via which
OL,20,Fchildren are able to access disturbing
OL,21,Fand extreme content."
